channel.title: Partially (5-10%) refactored 342 deob
channel.description:
I don't think a 342 has ever been released before, so I'm releasing it to you guys. I've never attempted to refactor (or even really work with) a client before, and I did this without any references, so please don't be too hard on my progress so far. :P
Thanks to Ethanofenjd for giving me the original deob. There's also a SVN being used to actively refactor it (PM me or post here if you'd like to help out): http://subversion.assembla.com/svn/342refactor/
